commit.message:
Switch out criterion for tasty-bench

Picking a build plan with both `foldable1-classes-compat` (as a local package)
and `criterion` was leading to cyclic dependencies, which `tasty-bench` avoids.
Allow building with base-4.19.*, deepseq-1.5.*, ghc-prim-0.11.*

CI: Use GHC 9.6.1-alpha3

This is the first alpha release to include a sufficiently recent version of
`transformers` that includes `Foldable1` instances.

Allow building with ghc-prim-0.10.*

Needed for GHC 9.6 support.

Use generic-deriving to define GHC.Generics instances unconditionally

Fixes #6.

Support building with `base-4.18.*` (GHC 9.6.*)

When building with `base-4.18.*` or later, we simply re-export `Data.Foldable1`
and `Data.Bifoldable1` from `base`.

Fixes #12.
Move proposal writeups to their own subdirectory

Depend on bifunctor-classes-compat instead of bifunctors

See the related discussion starting at
https://github.com/ekmett/semigroupoids/issues/130#issuecomment-1404285990
